<p>As more people explore the metaverse and buy virtual land, it could lead to a shift in how people view and value property. Additionally, real estate companies are beginning to experiment with virtual reality-based tours and experiences, providing new ways for buyers to explore properties without physically visiting them.</p>



<p>This emerging trend has the potential to change the dynamics of the traditional real estate market as technology continues to advance and more people embrace digital ownership.</p>



